{"talk":{"id":64428,"name":"Farish Ahmad-Noor: Why is colonialism (still) romanticized?","description":"Colonialism remains an inescapable blight on the present, lingering in the toxic, internalized mythologies and stereotypes that have outlived the regimes that created them, says historian Farish Ahmad-Noor. Examining why these prejudices and narratives persist (and sometimes thrive), he suggests a multidisciplinary approach to reject cultural obsessions with romanticized history and prevent this nostalgia from perpetuating past oppressions.","slug":"farish_ahmad_noor_why_is_colonialism_still_romanticized","recorded_at":"2019-09-28 00:00:00","published_at":"2020-06-23 15:20:15","updated_at":"2020-12-31 12:07:04","viewed_count":0,"emailed_count":0,"event":{"id":648,"name":"TEDxNTU"},"images":[{"image":{"size":"113x85","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/a3f089872c601a065141b0222be7496a904138f8_113x85.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"240x180","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/a3f089872c601a065141b0222be7496a904138f8_240x180.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"615x461","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/a3f089872c601a065141b0222be7496a904138f8_615x461.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"2400x1800","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/a3f089872c601a065141b0222be7496a904138f8_2400x1800.jpg"}}],"image_16x9":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/813c44caf8293ac96e70ddd17a43a11ce4293652_2880x1620.jpg","media":{"internal":{"64k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/FarishAhmadNoor_2019X-64k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":6088667,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"180k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/FarishAhmadNoor_2019X-180k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":16843507,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"320k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/FarishAhmadNoor_2019X-320k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":29870342,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"450k":{"